      "message": "for an approximate idea of how it\u0027d execute, there\u0027s also\n\n    builder.done().dump(\u0026stream)\n\nThat\u0027ll assign registers to values, and in the process count up how many registers we\u0027d need to never spill.  The JITs of course do spill to the stack if they don\u0027t have that many registers, but the interpreter will run just like this trace.  The \"instruction\" count is also kind of notional... really should be called \"ops\" I guess.  Mostly it\u0027s 1:1, but some of the ops you\u0027d see in this dump expand to more than one hardware instruction in the JITs, and splats() sometimes end up as zero instructions.",
